<s> I agree with Charles that the OBJECT element is much more flexible than the LONGDESC attribute, and that its use should be encouraged.  </s>
<s> The nested structure of OBJECT permits various alternative representations of a multimedia resource to be provided easily, including a written description with block-level markup.  </s>
<s> It should be remembered that LONGDESC is essentially an attempt to mittigate the access consequences resulting from the inadequacies of the IMG element, which were rectified in HTML 4.0 with the introduction of OBJECT.  </s>
